## M20i.1.1 (post-impl review): resource Vec iteration over a non-bare
## source is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5's M20i.1 post-implementation review (conversation entry
## 28): resource Vec iteration in V1 must have a bare local Vec
## binding as its source. Two reasons:
##
##   1. The ownership-layer loop-source read borrow only attaches to a
##      bare name. Iterating over a member access or call-result
##      temporary would leave the Vec un-borrowed, defeating the
##      mutation-during-iteration rejection rule.
##   2. A function-result temporary's buffer would be dropped at
##      statement end, freeing the elements mid-loop. Memory unsafety.
##
## The sema diagnostic points the user at the fix: bind the result
## to a `Vec(T)` local first.

fun makeSubs() -> Vec(*Closure())
  v: Vec(*Closure()) = Vec()
  <v

sub main()
  for cb in ?makeSubs()
    cb()
